details: The script uses SLURM to run a Python script utilizing the gswgan-pytorch conda environment. It requests access to the 'gpu20' partition with two GPUs. The script also sets up a conda environment using anaconda3 installed at '/BS/dchen-projects/work/Software/anaconda3/'. The main script being executed is 'main.py' with arguments related to dataset ('mnist'), model name ('ResNet_slurm_2GPUs'), number of GPUs (2), and output directory ('../results/mnist/pretrain/ResNet_default').
